trans-unit.source: Represents the data in a SOAP request or SOAP response at a specific <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Representerer dataene i SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret på en bestemt <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The primary use of the SoapMessage class is for SOAP extensions, representing the data in a SOAP request or SOAP response.
trans-unit.target: Klassen SoapMessage brukes i primær til SOAP-filtyper, som representerer dataene i SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret.

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A> method is called, a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension> receives a SoapMessage at each <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.
trans-unit.target: Når <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>-metoden, en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension>mottar en SoapMessage på hver <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>

trans-unit.source: It is up to the particular SOAP extension to choose how to process the SoapMessage.
trans-unit.target: Det er bestemt SOAP-utvidelsen skal kunne velge hvordan du vil behandle SoapMessage.

trans-unit.source: Common SOAP extensions include encryption and compression.
trans-unit.target: Vanlige SOAP-utvidelser inkluderer kryptering og komprimeringsinnstillinger.

trans-unit.source: SOAP extensions can be applied to either or both an XML Web service method created using ASP.NET or an XML Web service client.
trans-unit.target: SOAP-utvidelser kan brukes på en eller begge en XML-Web service-metode opprettet ved hjelp av ASP.NET, eller en XML-Web service-klienten.

trans-unit.source: When a SOAP extension is applied to an XML Web service method, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A> method receives an instance of <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage>, which derives from SoapMessage.
trans-unit.target: Når en SOAP-filtype brukes til en XML-Web service-metoden i <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>metoden mottar en forekomst av <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage>, som er avledet fra SoapMessage.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>

trans-unit.source: Likewise, when a SOAP extension is applied to an XML Web service client, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A> receives an instance of <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapClientMessage>.
trans-unit.target: På samme måte når en SOAP-filtype er brukt i en XML-Web service-klient <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>mottar en forekomst av <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapClientMessage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapClientMessage> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the SOAPAction HTTP request header field for the SOAP request or SOAP response.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter feltet SOAPAction HTTP-forespørselen topptekst for SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret.

trans-unit.source: The Action property can be accessed during any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen kan åpnes under noen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: The SOAPAction HTTP request header field for the SOAP request or SOAP response.
trans-unit.target: SOAPAction HTTP-forespørselsfeltet topptekst for SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the contents of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Encoding" name="Content-Encoding" href=""></xref> HTTP header.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir innholdet i den <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Encoding" name="Content-Encoding" href=""> </xref> HTTP-hode.

trans-unit.source: A SOAP extension can set the ContentEncoding property to provide supplementary information about the encoding of a SOAP message without changing the media type as expressed in the `Content-Type` HTTP header.
trans-unit.target: Et SOAP-filtypen kan angi egenskapen ContentEncoding å formidle tilleggsinformasjon om kodingen for en SOAP-melding uten å endre medietypen uttrykt i den `Content-Type` HTTP-hode.

trans-unit.source: The contents of the <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Encoding" name="Content-Encoding" href=""></xref> HTTP header.
trans-unit.target: Innholdet i den <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Encoding" name="Content-Encoding" href=""> </xref> HTTP-hode.

trans-unit.source: The current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> is <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> stages.
trans-unit.target: The current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> is <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> stages.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the HTTP <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Type" name="Content-Type" href=""></xref> of the SOAP request or SOAP response.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir HTTP <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Type" name="Content-Type" href=""> </xref> i SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret.

trans-unit.source: The ContentType property can only be accessed in the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> and <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stages; otherwise, an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> is thrown.
trans-unit.target: ContentType-egenskapen kan bare brukes i den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>og <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>Salgssyklusfaser; ellers en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>forårsakes.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: Use the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage.ContentEncoding%2A> property, instead of the ContentType property to provide supplementary information about the encoding of a SOAP message.
trans-unit.target: Bruk av <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage.ContentEncoding%2A>egenskapen i stedet for ContentType-egenskapen for å formidle tilleggsinformasjon om kodingen for en SOAP-melding.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage.ContentEncoding%2A>

trans-unit.source: The HTTP <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Type" name="Content-Type" href=""></xref> of the SOAP request or SOAP response.
trans-unit.target: HTTP <xref uid="langword_csharp_Content-Type" name="Content-Type" href=""> </xref> i SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret.

trans-unit.source: The default is "text/xml".
trans-unit.target: Standarden er "text/xml".

trans-unit.source: ContentType is accessed <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> stages.
trans-unit.target: ContentType åpnes <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> faser.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, asserts that the current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> is a stage where in parameters are available.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, deklarasjoner som gjeldende <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> er et trinn der i parametere er tilgjengelig.

trans-unit.source: The asserted stage is different for XML Web service clients and XML Web service methods.
trans-unit.target: Påståtte fase er forskjellig for XML-Web service-klienter og metoder for XML.

trans-unit.source: An XML Web service method's in parameters are available after the SOAP request is deserialized in the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage.
trans-unit.target: Et XML-Web service for metoden i parametere er tilgjengelige når SOAP-forespørselen er deserialiseres i den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: For an XML Web service client, the in parameters are available prior to the SOAP request serialization process in the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage.
trans-unit.target: En XML-Web service-klient i parameterne er tilgjengelige før SOAP-forespørselen serialisering prosessen i den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: EnsureInStage can be called during any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>, however an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> is thrown when in parameters are not available.
trans-unit.target: EnsureInStage kan kalles under noen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>, men en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>et når i parametere er ikke tilgjengelig.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: In parameters are not available.
trans-unit.target: I parametere er ikke tilgjengelig.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, asserts that the current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> stage is a stage where out parameters are available.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, deklarasjoner som gjeldende <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> fase er et trinn der ut parametere er tilgjengelig.

trans-unit.source: The asserted stage is different for XML Web service clients and XML Web service methods.
trans-unit.target: Påståtte fase er forskjellig for XML-Web service-klienter og metoder for XML.

trans-unit.source: An XML Web service method's out parameters are available prior to the SOAP response serialization process in the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage.
trans-unit.target: Et XML-Web service for metoden ut parametere er tilgjengelige før SOAP svar serialisering prosessen i den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: In an XML Web service client, the out parameters are available after the SOAP response deserialization process in the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage.
trans-unit.target: En XML-Web service-klienten parameterne er tilgjengelig etter SOAP svar deserialisering prosessen i den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: EnsureOutStage can be called during any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>, however an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> is thrown when out parameters are not available.
trans-unit.target: EnsureOutStage kan kalles under noen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>, men en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>forårsakes når parametere er ikke tilgjengelig.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: Out parameters are not available.
trans-unit.target: Ut parametere er ikke tilgjengelig.

trans-unit.source: Ensures that the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> of the call to the XML Web service method is the stage or stages passed in.
trans-unit.target: Sikrer at den <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> i kallet til XML-Web service-metoden er fase eller faser sendt.

trans-unit.source: If the current processing stage is not one of the stages passed in, an exception is thrown.
trans-unit.target: Hvis gjeldende behandling fase ikke er ett av trinnene innsendte, er det et unntaket.

trans-unit.source: Multiple stages can be asserted by performing a bitwise OR operation on multiple instances of the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> class.
trans-unit.target: Flere faser kan være deklarert ved å utføre en bitvis OR-operasjon på flere forekomster av <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>klassen.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: EnsureStage can be called during any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.

trans-unit.source: The current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> is not the asserted stage or stages.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"> </xref> er ikke påståtte fase eller faser.

trans-unit.target: Henter en verdi som angir den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapDocumentMethodAttribute.OneWay%2A?displayProperty=fullName> egenskapen enten den <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapDocumentMethodAttribute"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapRpcMethodAttribute"> </xref> attributtet som brukes til XML Web service-metoden.

trans-unit.source: Gets the version of the SOAP protocol used to communicate with the XML Web service.
trans-unit.target: Henter versjonen av SOAP-protokollen som brukes til å kommunisere med XML-webtjenesten.

trans-unit.source: For a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage>, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage.SoapVersion%2A> property is guaranteed to be valid after the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage.
trans-unit.target: For en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage.SoapVersion%2A>egenskapen garanteres skal være gyldig etter den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage.SoapVersion%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapServerMessage>

trans-unit.source: In the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage> stage the property is available, however the SOAP message has not been completely processed and SOAP extensions that may alter the contents of the SOAP message have not run.
trans-unit.target: I de <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>fase egenskapen er tilgjengelig, men SOAP-meldingen ikke er fullstendig behandlet og SOAP-utvidelser som kan føre til at innholdet i SOAP-meldingen ble ikke kjørt.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: One of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapProtocolVersion"></xref> values.
trans-unit.target: Én av de <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapProtocolVersion"> </xref> verdier.

trans-unit.source: The default is <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapProtocolVersion"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Standard <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapProtocolVersion"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The Stage property can be accessed at any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen fase kan få tilgang til alle <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.target: The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage"></xref>.

trans-unit.source: Gets the data representing the SOAP request or SOAP response in the form of a <xref:System.IO.Stream>.
trans-unit.target: Henter data som representerer SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret i form av en <xref:System.IO.Stream>.</xref:System.IO.Stream>

trans-unit.source: SOAP extensions that inspect the data representing a SOAP request or SOAP response, such as a logging SOAP extension, can use the `Stream` property to view the data at each <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.
trans-unit.target: SOAP-utvidelser som undersøkes data som representerer en SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret, for eksempel logging SOAP-utvidelsen, kan bruke den `Stream` til å vise dataene på hver <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: SOAP extensions that modify the data representing a SOAP request or SOAP response, such as encryption or compression SOAP extensions, should do so with the <xref:System.IO.Stream> passed into the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A> method of <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension>.
trans-unit.target: SOAP-utvidelser som endrer data som representerer en SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret, for eksempel kryptering eller komprimering SOAP-filtyper, må gjøre dette med som er <xref:System.IO.Stream>sendt til <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A>metoden for <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A> </xref:System.IO.Stream>

trans-unit.source: The Stream property of <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage> passed into <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A> is read-only.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen dataflyten for <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage>ble sendt til <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A>er skrivebeskyttet.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ProcessMessage%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessage>

trans-unit.source: For more information on modifying the data representing a SOAP request or SOAP response, see <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon om hvordan du endrer data som representerer en SOAP-forespørselen eller SOAP-svaret, kan du se <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapExtension.ChainStream%2A>

trans-unit.source: A read-only instance of the <xref:System.IO.Stream> class.
trans-unit.target: En skrivebeskyttet forekomst av <xref:System.IO.Stream>klassen.</xref:System.IO.Stream>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the base URL of the XML Web service.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter den primære URL-adressen for XML-webtjenesten.

trans-unit.source: The Url property can be accessed during any <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.
trans-unit.target: URL-egenskapen kan åpnes under noen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapMessageStage>

trans-unit.source: The base URL of the XML Web service.
trans-unit.target: Den primære URL-adressen for XML-webtjenesten.
